Package: SASfromR
Type: Package
Title: Execute SAS-Code From Within R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Jens", "Michelsen",
      email = "jens.michelsen@tuta.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: This package allows you to run SAS code (through batch-mode) from within R.
    Datasets are made available to SAS through integration with the `haven`-package, and results can similarly be imported back into R.
    Logs and output can be viewed directly from the R console for a more interactive workflow and debugging.
    All in one call (requires a working installation of SAS).
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Imports: 
    haven,
    readr,
    stringr,
    cli
